@node "Introduction" "Introduction"

@{MS "Introduction"}

ArakAttack is an USB driver for the Poseidon USB Stack in combination with any common USB controller hardware.@{par}

@endnode
@node "Systemrequirements" "Systemrequirements"

@{MS "System requirements"}

Amiga OS 3.x and an AmigaOS compatible system with PCI ports.@{par}

The latest version of Chris Hodges' Poseidon USB Stack. http://www.platon42.de/poseidon.html@{par}

In addition to that other components are required:

 @{MC "Amithlon"}

powerpci.library  V2.14 or better. http://vmc.de/amithlon

 @{MC "Amiga"}

openpci.library V2.00 or better. http://www.chez.com/titan/OpenPciUK.html

@endnode
@node "Featurelist" "Features"

@{MS "Features"}

° Amithlon optimised version.@{par}

° OpenPCI compatible version.@{par}

° UHCI controller support. (incl. on board)@{par}

° OHCI controller support. (incl. on board)@{par}

° EHCI controller support. (incl. on board)@{par}

° Unlimited number of usb controllers supported at the same time.@{par}

° Unlimited number of parallel usb transfers garantees maximum performance.@{par}

° Only one device with multiple units makes installation very easy.@{par}

° Intelligent transfer descriptor caching mechanism.@{par}

° Full mem handler support. (Frees resources and caches if the system signals low system memory)@{par}

° No HUB depth limits.@{par}

° Separate time out handling for each USB request garantees the driver never freezes the usb stack or the system.@{par}

° External interrupt fallback for systems with interrupt latency trouble.@{par}

@endnode
