@node "HowToInstall" "How to install ArakAttack"

@{MS "How to install ArakAttack"}

Just use the included installer script to install this driver paket!@{par}

@{b}Don't try to install this archive by hand, because this will cause many
trouble. The automatic installation ensures a minimum use of disc and memory
space!@{ub}

@endnode
@node "Quickstart" "How to get it work?"

@{MS "How to get it work?"}

If Poseidon V2.2 was present when installing ArakAttack and when you selected
create config within the installer, then additional configuration is not
required.@{par}

After installing the driver just start Trident (included in the Poseidon
archive). This tool normaly is stored within "sys:prefs/".@{par}

Now press "new", push the file selector gadget and select "AmithlonUSB.device"
or "OpenUSB.device". If both devices are listed, then you didn't use the
installer script. In such case install the driver correct by using the installer
script.@{par}

Now press the copy button and select the new entry. This time just increase the
value within the unit field behind the device text field. Repeat this step 5
times.@{par}

Now the list should contain five entries with different units (0-4). Now you can
push the "online" button and see what happens. After a few seconds the "In use"
section should be changing from "no" to "yes".@{par}

Some entries may still be at the "no" state. This entries can be removed,
because there is no controller for this unit. If all five units are in "yes"
state, then you probably can add more units. Just add additional entries and push
online again. Don't worry! You can't burn anything. Just try it!@{par}

I can't tell you how many entries you'll get. This depends on the number of USB
controller within your system and their type.@{par}

Finaly save the settings. Now you should restart Trident and select the devices
page. Now you can plug in a device and you should see a result.@{par}

More information can be found within the Poseidon manual.@{par}

@endnode
